'''Eguadoto Afahyɛ''' afehyia [[afahyɛ]] a ahenfo ne wɔn manfoɔ a wɔn wɔ Nfanteman mu wɔ Nfinfin Manatam wɔ Ghana no di. Wodi saa afahyɛ yi wɔ bosome ɛtɔ so nwɔtwe no mu<ref>https://www.easytrackghana.com/cultural-overview-ghana-festivals.php</ref><ref name="ghanareview.com">http://ghanareview.com/festivals2.html</ref><ref name="ghanareview.com"/>. Gomoa Ajumakofo a ɛbɛn Apam no nso yɛ nea wodi saa afahyɛ yi bi <ref>https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/Traditional-ruler-cautions-against-installation-of-foreigners-as-chiefs-251639</ref><ref>https://newsghana.com.gh/traditional-ruler-cautions-against-installation-of-foreigners-as-chiefs/</ref>. Gomoa Pomadzefo nso yɛ nea wodi afahyɛ no<ref>https://www.modernghana.com/news/716783/lets-intensify-education-on-peaceful-election.html</ref>

== Afa hyɛ ==
Wɔde nnuane ne nsa gye ahohoɔ wɔ afahyɛ no ase. Amanfoɔ no hyɛ wɔn amammerɛ ntadeɛ ahorɔw de kɔ dwa dataa a ahenfo no abɔ no ase. Asa ne nnwomtoɔ nso kɔ so wɔ afahyɛ no ase<ref>http://www.ghanaembassyiran.com/en/page/majorfestivals</ref>.

== Mfasɔ ==
Wodi saa afahyɛ yi de te wɔn abosom nkonnwa no na wɔsan nam afahyɛ no so kyerɛ sɛ bayerɛ foforo mmere aso ama ɔkɔm bere aba awie<ref>http://www.s158663955.websitehome.co.uk/ghanaculture/mod_print.php?archiveid=234</ref><ref>https://touringghana.com/festivals/</ref><ref>https://books.google.com.gh/books?id=EkpNAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA648&lpg=PA648&dq=eguadoto+festival&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=eguadoto%20festival&f=false</ref>.

